question: Will PC win the most in the 2024 New Brunswick general election?
description:
The Canadian province of New Brunswick has scheduled a general election for October 21, 2024.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if PC (Progressive Conservative Party of New Brunswick) controls a greater number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick than any other party after the results of the 2024 New Brunswick general election are finalized. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If the results of this election aren't known by March 31, 2025, 11:59PM ET, this market will resolve to "No".

In the case of a tie between this party and any other for the most seats controlled, this market will resolve in favor of the party whose listed name comes first in alphabetical order.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the New Brunswick government and/or information published by Elections New Brunswick (https://www.electionsnb.ca/content/enb/en.html). However, a consensus of credible media reports will also suffice to resolve this market.
